This paper deals with the segmentation of trees within a forest canopy using LiDAR point clouds. LiDAR point clouds are commonly used in computer vision and graphics applications, which suggests that this paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach for stratifying the point cloud to overstory and understory canopy layers, which involves analyzing the vertical distribution of LiDAR points. This approach could be considered a machine learning or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) method. Additionally, the paper evaluates the segmentation results using statistical analysis, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) or robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.RO, in that order.
